Prasada Stupa
This small stupa lies between the 
 and the 
 of 
in 
. It is built surrounding a small rock and belongs to the Prasada type of Stupa similar to the 
 in 
. These have a square base instead of the usual circular base and are common in Thailand.
The original name of the Stupa is not known but now it is known as Prasada Stupa. Locally it is also known as 
 and also as the Tomb of King Dutugemunu. Only a part of the stupa remains today including some remains of the Image House. It is believed that this stupa belongs to the late Anuradhapura Period.
